        <!-- Storage Tips -->
        <div class="section">
            <h2>Storage Tips</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><b>Store spices properly:</b> Keep spices in airtight containers away from heat and direct sunlight to preserve their flavor for longer.</li>
                <li><b>Freeze herbs in oil:</b> Chop fresh herbs, place them in an ice cube tray, and fill with olive oil. Freeze and use as needed for soups and sauces.</li>
                <li><b>Keep vegetables fresh:</b> Wrap leafy greens in a paper towel before placing them in a plastic bag to keep them crisp longer.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Meal Prep Hacks -->
        <div class="section">
            <h2>Meal Prep Hacks</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><b>Chop once, use twice:</b> When chopping vegetables, prep extra for the next day to save time.</li>
                <li><b>Batch cook grains:</b> Cook rice, quinoa, or pasta in bulk and store in the fridge for quick meals throughout the week.</li>
                <li><b>Pre-portion ingredients:</b> Pre-measure ingredients for recipes and store them in containers to save time during cooking.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Cooking Shortcuts -->
        <div class="section">
            <h2>Cooking Shortcuts</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><b>Peel garlic easily:</b> Microwave garlic cloves for 10 seconds, and the peel will slide right off.</li>
                <li><b>Keep knives sharp:</b> Use a honing rod regularly to maintain your knives and speed up your chopping.</li>
                <li><b>Use parchment paper:</b> Line baking sheets with parchment paper for easy cleanup.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Baking Tips -->
        <div class="section">
            <h2>Baking Tips</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><b>Room temperature ingredients:</b> Bring butter and eggs to room temperature before baking for better mixing and fluffier results.</li>
                <li><b>Prevent sticky measuring cups:</b> Spray measuring cups with oil before measuring sticky ingredients like honey or syrup.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- General Kitchen Hacks -->
        <div class="section">
            <h2>General Kitchen Hacks</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><b>Clean as you go:</b> Save time by washing utensils and wiping surfaces as you cook.</li>
                <li><b>Organize your workspace:</b> Keep frequently used tools like knives, spatulas, and measuring spoons within reach for efficiency.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
